  "Sanctions" : "Respondent understands that this settlement includes a finding that he failed to supervise an individual who violated Section 10(b) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 and that under Article III, Section 4 of FINRA's By-Laws, this makes him subject to a statutory disqualification with respect to association with a member.",
  "Regulator Statement" : "Consequently, the firm and its representative, the one who Champney failed to reasonably supervise from engaging in the churning and unsuitable excessive trading in the retired 93-year-old customer's accounts, made a settlement payment totaling $470,000 to the guardian for the retired customer's accounts. In addition, FINRA barred the representative, whom Champney failed to reasonably supervise, from associating with any FINRA member firm in any capacity in FINRA AWC Case No. 2015045984001. Fines paid in full on August 13, 2018.",
